Package com.bakdata.dedupe.clustering

Class Cluster<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>,​T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bakdata.dedupe.clustering.Cluster<C,​T>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - the type of the cluster id.
    T - the type of the records.
    public class Cluster<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>,​T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A cluster is a coherent collection of duplicate records.

    All records inside the cluster are deemed to be pair-wise duplicates. No record outside the cluster is a duplicate with any record inside the cluster.

    Any dataset can be divided into an exhaustive set of non-overlapping clusters with a Classifier and Clustering. In that sense, the duplicate relation becomes a mathematical partitioning of the dataset.

    In general, a cluster returned by the Clustering should always contain at least one element. Temporarily, a cluster may be constructed without elements.
